Ginge or ginge root is the rhizome o the plant Zingiber officinale, consumed as a delicacy, medicine, or spice.
The abacus, an aa cried a coontin frame, is a calculatin tuil uised primarily in pairts o Asie for performin arithmetic processes.
Phytoplankton are the autotrophic components o the plankton commonty an a key part o oceans, seas an freshwatter basin ecoseestems.
The capybara is the lairgest rodent in the warld, follaed bi the beaver, porcupine, an mara.
The even-taed ungulates are ungulates whose wicht is borne aboot equally bi the third an fowert taes, rather than maistly or entirely bi the third as in odd-taed ungulates, such as horse.
An odd-taed ungulate is a mammal wi huifs that featur an odd nummer o taes.
Kohlrabi is an annual vegetable, an is a law, fodgle cultivar o cabbitch.
Plants that growes in the sea.
The leek, Allium ampeloprasum var.
An epiphyte is an organism that growes on the surface o a plant an sorns its moistur an nutrients frae the air, rain, watter or frae the glaur bingin up around it.
The spermatophytes comprise those plants that produce seeds.
Asparagus officinalis is a spring vegetable, a flouerin perennial plant species in the genus Asparagus.
Broccoli is a plant, Brassica oleracea.
The flouerin plants, an aa kent as Angiospermae Lindl.
The gymnosperms is a group o seed-producin plants that includes conifers, cycads, Ginkgo, an Gnetales.
Amanita muscaria, commonly kent as the flee agaric or flee amanita, is a puddock stuil an psychoactive basidiomycete fungus, ane o mony in the genus Amanita.
Solanum dulcamara, forby kent as pushion berry, mad dug’s berries, puir-man's-wather-gless, is a species o vine in the potato genus Solanum, faimily Solanaceae.
Groose is a group of birds in the faimily Galliformes.
The grizzly beir, less commonly kent as the sillertip beir, is a muckle subspecies o broun beir inhabitin North Americae.
Spiders are air-braithin arthropods that hae aicht legs an chelicerae wi fangs that inject venom.
Taxus baccata is a conifer native tae wastren, central an soothren Europe, northwast Africae, northren Iran an soothwast Asie.
Cyanobacteria /saɪˌænoʊbækˈtɪəriə/, forby kent as Cyanophyta, is a phylum o bacteria that obtain thair energy throu photosynthesis.
Algae are a very muckle an diverse group o simple, typically autotrophic organisms, rangin frae unicellular tae multicellular furms, such as the giant kelp, that mey grow up tae 50 meters in length.
Crinoids are marine ainimals that mak up the class Crinoidea, ane o the clesses o the phylum Echinodermata, that an aw includes the starfish, brittle starns, sea urchins an sea cucumbers.
A tunicate is a marine invertebrate ainimal, a member o the subphylum Tunicata, which is pairt o the Chordata, a phylum which includes aw ainimals wi dorsal nerve cords an notochords.
Ceratosaurus wis a predatory theropod dinosaur in the Late Jurassic Period.
Sponges are not ainimals o the phylum Porifera.
The garfish, or sea needle, is a pelagic, oceanodromous needlefish foond in brackish an marine watters o the Atlantic Ocean an the Mediterranean, Caribbean, Black, an Baltic Seas.
The thylacine wis the lairgest kent carnivorous marsupial o modren times.
The doiterel, an aa Eurasie doiterel, is a smaw wader in the pliver faimily o birds.
Adalia bipunctata is a carnivorous clock leddy o the faimily Coccinellidae that is foond ootthrou the holarctic region.

The reid panda, also cried the lesser panda an reid cat-bear, is a smaw mammal native tae the eastren Himalayas an sooth-wast Cheenae that haes been classified as an Endangered bi IUCN as its wild population is estimatit at less nor 10,000 mature individuals.
The reid wouf, forby kent as the Florida wouf or Mississippi Valley wouf is a canid o unresolved taxonomic identity native tae the eastren Unitit States.
Lizards is reptiles o the faimily Squamata, that for ordinar haes fower legs an external lug opening.
Rodents are mammals o the order Rodentia, characterised bi a single pair o continuously growin incisors in ilka o the upper an lawer jaws that must be kept short bi gnawin.
Bum-bees or bummlers is sindry species o bee in the genus Bombus sic as the white airsie, or, the reid airsie, the foggie-bee, the brounie an the gairy-bee.
Salmonella /ˌsælməˈnɛlə/ is a genus o rod-shaped, Gram-negative bacteria.
The cocoa bean, an aa cacao bean or simply cocoa or cacao, is the dried an fully fermented fatty seed o Theobroma cacao, frae which cocoa solits an cocoa butter can be extractit.
Sea urchins or urchins, sometimes cried sea hedgehogs, are smaa, spiny, globular animals which, wi thair close kin, such as saund dollars, constitute the class Echinoidea o the echinoderm phylum.
Penguins are a group o aquatic, flightless birds livin almaist exclusively in the Soothren Hemisphere, especially in Antarctica.
The muff cock or muckle snippock is a medium-smaw wadin bird foond in temperate an subarctic Eurasie.
A lynx is ony o the fower species within the Lynx genus o medium-sized wildcats.
The Mandarin oranger, forby kent as the mandarin or mandarine, is a smaa citrus tree wi fruit resemblin ither orangers.
The garnet is a fruit-beirin deciduous shrub in the faimily Lythraceae, subfaimily Punicoideae, that growes atween 5 an 10 m taw.
An Nabk or Al-Nabk is a Sirie ceety admeenistratively belangin tae the Rif Dimashq Govrenorate an the caipital o the Qalamoun.
Acer campestre, kent as the field maple, is a flouerin plant species in the soapberry an lychee faimily Sapindaceae.
Taxus cuspidata is a member o the genus Taxus, native tae Japan, Korea, northeast Cheenae an the extreme sootheast o Roushie.
Salvia officinalis is a perennial, evergreen subscrog, wi widdy stems, grayochie leafs, an blue tae purpiochie flouers.
The great white pelican forby kent as the Eastern White Pelican, Rosy Pelican or White Pelican is a bird in the pelican faimily.
The langfin mako shairk is a species o mackerel shairk in the faimily Lamnidae, wi a probable warldwide distribution in temperate an tropical watters.
The okapi, Okapia johnstoni, is a giraffid artiodactyl mammal native tae the Ituri Rainforest, locatit in the northeast o the Democratic Republic o the Congo, in Central Africae.
Bacteria constitute a muckle domain or kinrick o prokaryotic microorganisms.
The dugong is a medium-sized marine mammal.
The blue shairk is a species o requiem shairk, in the faimily Carcharhinidae, that inhabits deep watters in the warld's temperate an tropical oceans.

The gerenuk, Litocranius walleri, kent as the Waller's gazelle an aw, is a lang-necked species o antelope foond in dry thorn bush scrub an desert in East Africae, frae Somalie, Djibouti an eastren Ethiopie throu northren an eastren Kenyae tae northeastren Tanzanie.
The Hornit houlet is a speshie o houlet that leeves in Europe, Asie, an North Americae.
The serval /ˈsɜːrvəl/ is a medium-sized African wild cat.
The brumple is an eel-lik fish foond in the intertidal an subtidal zones o the North Atlantic.
The koala is an arboreal herbivorous marsupial native tae Australie.
Beasties is a cless o hexapod invertebrates within the arthropod phylum that haes a chitinous exoskeleton, a three-pairt bouk, three pairs o jyntit legs, compoond een an ae pair o antennae.
The narwhal, or narwhaul, is a medium-sized tuithed whaul that lives year-roond in the Arctic.
The numbat, kent as the bandit anteater, marsupial anteater, or walpurti an aa, is a marsupial foond in Wastren Australie.
Puffinus puffinus is a medium-sized shearwatter in the seabird faimily Procellariidae.
The pirr-maw or pick-maw is a smaw gou that breeds in much o Europe an Asie, an aa in coastal eastren Canadae.
Catshairks are grund shairks o the faimily Scyliorhinidae.
The Whitrat or wheasel o the genus Mustela, is a smaw carnivore.
The Viverridae is a faimily o smaa tae medium-sized mammals, the viverrids, comprisin 15 genera, which are subdividit intae 33 species.
Calidris alpina is a smaw wader, whiles separatit wi the ither "stints" in Erolia.
A grebe /ˈɡriːb/ is a member o the Podicipediformes order, a widely distributit order o freshwatter divin birds, some o which veesit the sea when migratin an in winter.
The ware guiss is a species o guiss o the genus Branta.
The platypus, cried the deuk-billed platypus an aa, is a semiaquatic egg-layin mammal endemic tae eastren Australie, includin Tasmanie.
The Gowdspink or Gowdie is a wee birdie that's weel kent as gairden birds in Scotland an haes a fondness for the seeds o the thristle an the taisle.
The Acrocephalus schoenobaenus is an Auld Warld warbler in the genus Acrocephalus.
Spergula arvensis, kent as yarr or melkie is a species o plant in the genus Spergula.
The Rock hawk is a smaa species o falcon frae the Northren Hemisphere.
Sardina pilchardus is a speshies o ray-finned fish in the monotypic genus Sardina.
Quail is a collective name for several genera o mid-sized birds generally placed in the order Galliformes.
The gorals are fower speshies in the genus Nemorhaedus or Naemorhedus.
The gowdfish is a freshwatter fish in the faimily Cyprinidae o order Cypriniformes.
The European rae deer, an aa kent as the wastren rae deer, chevreuil, or rae deer, is an Eurasie species o deer.
The kit tod is a tod species o North Americae.
The hoose sparrae, or spur, is a bird o the sparrae faimily Passeridae, foond in maist pairts o the warld.
The mustang is a free-roamin horse o the American wast that first descendit frae horse brocht tae the Americas bi the Spaingie.
The tits, chickadees, an titmice constitute the Paridae, a muckle faimily o smaa passerine birds which occur in the Northren Hemisphere an Africae.
The keeng's fisher is a bird wi seiven subspecies recognised within its wide distribution athort Eurasie an North Africae.
The ring-tailed lemur is a muckle strepsirrhine primate an the maist recognised lemur due tae its lang, black an white ringed tail.
The dachshund is a short-legged, lang-bodied dug breed belangin tae the hoond faimily.
The bobcat is a North American cat that appeared durin the Irvingtonian stage o aroond 1.8 million years ago.
Laurus nobilis is an aromatic uvergreen tree or lairge shrub wi green, glabrous leafs, in the flouerin plant faimily Lauraceae.
A screw, kent as a shirrow forby, is a wee creatir sae like a moose an sib tae voles.
The hurcheon is a wee mammal o the subfaimily Erinaceinae.
A pseudoscorpion,, is an arachnid belangin tae the order Pseudoscorpionida, forby kent as Pseudoscorpiones or Chelonethida.

Corylus avellana, the common hazel or hizzle, is a species o hazel native tae Europe an wastren Asie, frae the Breetish Isles sooth tae Iberie, Greece, Turkey an Cyprus, north tae central Scandinavie, an east tae the central Ural Moontains, the Caucasus, an northwastren Iran.
The Cheenese alligator is ane o twa kent livin species o Alligator, a genus in the faimily Alligatoridae.
A tenrec is ony species o mammal within the faimily Tenrecidae, foond on Madagascar an in pairts o the African mainland.
The broun hawk is a bird o prey species alanging tae the kestrel group o the falcon faimily Falconidae.
The Lintie or lintwhite is a wee bird in the finch faimily Fringillidae.

The African Penguin, kent forbye as the Jackass Penguin, is fand on the sooth-wastern strand o Africae, bidin in colonies on 24 islands aqueesh Namibie an Algoa Bay, naur Port Elizabeth, Sooth Africae.

An Esk is a wee ainimal, a kynd o salamander.
A piranha or piraña is a member o faimily Characidae in order Characiformes, an omnivorous freshwatter fish that inhabits Sooth American rivers.
The vicuña or vicugna is ane o twa wild Sooth American camelids which live in the heich alpine auries o the Andes, the ither bein the guanaco.
Deuk is the common name for several speshie o birds in the faimily Anatidae.
The coyote is a canid native tae North Americae.
Darwin's rhea, an aw kent as the lesser rhea, is a lairge flichtless bird, but the smawer o the twa extant speshies o rheas.

The horse is ane o twa extant subspecies o Equus ferus.
A Throstle is for ordinar a bird that's a member o the faimlie Turdidae.

The Bengal teeger, cried the Ryal Bengal teeger an aw, is the maist numerous teeger subspecies.

Staphylococcus is a genus o Gram-positive bacteria.

Swans are birds o the faimily Anatidae within the genus Cygnus.
The silkworm is the larva or caterpeelar o the domesticatit silkmoch, Bombyx mori.
Deinonychus is a genus o carnivorous dromaeosaurid dinosaurs.
Maukins, whiles kent as donies or bawds, are smaw yerbivorous mammals sib tae kinnens.
Maize, kent as corn an aw, is a herbaceous plant domesticatit in Mesoamericae that syne spreid athort the American continents.

Fraxinus excelsior — kent as the esh, or European esh or common esh tae distinguish it frae ether types o esh — is a species o Fraxinus native tae maist o Europe wi the exception o northren Scandinavie an soothren Iberie, an also soothwestren Asie frae northren Turkey east tae the Caucasus an Alborz muntains.

Typha latifolia is a perennial yerbaceous plant in the genus Typha.
Chamaenerion angustifolium is a perennial yerbaceous plant in the faimily Onagraceae.
Juncus effusus, wi the common names bog-spret or floss, is a perennial yerbaceous flouerin plant species in the faimily Juncaceae.
Phoenix dactylifera, commonly kent as date or date paum, is a flouerin plant speshies in the paum faimily, Arecaceae, cultivatit for its edible sweet fruit.
Prunus armeniaca, the maist commonly cultivatit apricot species, cried ansu apricot, Siberian apricot, Tibetan apricot an aw, is a species o Prunus, clessifee'd wi the ploum in the subgenus Prunus.
Plankton are the diverse collection o organisms that leeve in the watter column o muckle bouks o watter an are unable tae soum against a current.
The Bizzart is a middlin tae lairge bird o prey, whose range covers maist o Europe an extends intae Asie.
The Turtle-doo or Turtour, kent forbye as the European Turtle Doo, is a memmer o the bird faimily Columbidae.
The loch maw is a medium-sized gou which breeds in northren Asie, northren Europe an northwastren North Americae.

The reid tod is the lairgest o the true tods an the maist abundant member o the Carnivora, bein distributit across the entire Northren Hemisphere frae the Arctic Circle tae North Africae, Central Americae an Asie.
The herbour dunter is ane o sax species o porpoise.
The white stork, eften semply cried stork, is a lairge bird in the stork faimily, Ciconiidae.
The stoat-wheasel or Scots ermine is a wee mammal o the faimily Mustelidae.
The Komodo draigon, kent as the Komodo monitor an aw, is a lairge species o lizard foond in the Indonesie islands o Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, an Padar.
The Emperor Penguin is the heichest an hiviest o aw livin penguin species an is endemic tae Antarcticae.
Monotremes are mammals that lay eggs insteid o givin birth tae live young lik marsupials an placental mammals.
Minnie Mouse is a funny animal cartuin character creatit bi Ub Iwerks an Walt Disney.
Mycoplasma is a genus o bacteria that lack a cell waw aroond thair cell membrane.
The brammle is a widespreid buss, an kenspeckle group o ower 375 speshies, o sib apomictic microspeshies that's hamelt aw ower the temperate Northren hemisphere an Sooth Americae.
The human immunodeficiency virus is a lentivirus that causes HIV infection an acquired immunodeficiency syndrome.

The Arctic tod, spelled Airctic tod an aw, kent as the white tod, polar tod, or snaw tod an aw, is a smaa tod native tae the Arctic regions o the Northren Hemisphere an common throuoot the Arctic tundra biome.
Fog, kent forbye as moss, is sindry wee, saft plaunts that's fer ordinar 1–10 cm lang, tho some species is mair muckle.
Pangolins are mammals o the order Pholidota.
The poinsettia is a culturally an commercially important plant species o the diverse spurge faimily that is indigenous tae Mexico an Central Americae.
Agave is a genus o monocots.
The papaya /pəˈpaɪə/ or /pəˈpɑːjə/, papaw, or pawpaw is the fruit o the plant Carica papaya, the sole species in the genus Carica o the plant faimily Caricaceae.
Theobroma cacao an aa cacao tree an cocoa tree, is a smaa evergreen tree in the faimily Malvaceae, native tae the deep tropical regions o Central an Sooth Americae.
Hops is the female flouer cones o the hop plant.
The Bactrie camel is a muckle, even-taed ungulate native tae the steppes o Central Asie.
Midges are a faimily o smaa, flees: the Culicidae.
Flees is insects o the Order Diptera, that hase ae pair o wings on the mesothorax an a pair o halteres, derived frae the hind wings, on the metathorax.
Mochs or -bats is wee beasties sib tae butterflees.
Berberis vulgaris L., forby kent as wine or guil-tree, is a buss in the genus Berberis.
Saccharomyces cerevisiae is a species o baurm.
Paurits or papingaes, kent as psittacines an aa, are birds o the aboot 372 species in 86 genera that mak up the order Psittaciformes, foond in maist tropical an subtropical regions.
Tortoises are a faimily, Testudinidae, o laund-dwallin reptiles in the order Testudines.
Latrodectus mactans, or Soothren black widow or simply black widow, is a heichly venomous species o speeder in the genus Latrodectus.
The Boa constrictor is a species o muckle, hivy-bodied snake.
The Great Dane is a German breed o domestic dug kent for its giant size.
Compsognathus is a genus o smaa, bipedal, carnivorous theropod dinosaurs.

Clematis vitalba is a shrub o the Ranunculaceae faimily.

Birds are a group o endothermic vertebrates, characterised bi feathers, tuithless beakit jaws, the layin o haurd-shelled eggs, a heich metabolic rate, a fower-chaumbered hert, and a lichtweicht bit pure tough skelet.
A vine is ony plant wi a growthe habit o trailin or scandent stems, lianas or rinners.
Geese are watterfoul alangin tae the tribe Anserini o the faimily Anatidae.
Baleen whauls are a widely distributit an diverse parvorder o carnivorous marine mammals.
The polar beir is a carnivorous beir whase native range lies lairgely within the Arctic Circle, encompassin the Arctic Ocean, its surroondin seas an surroondin laund masses.
The Sulphur-crestit Cockatoo is a relatively lairge white cockatoo foond in widit habitats in Australie an New Guinea an some o the islands o Indonesie.
The swart-back, kent as the gou maw or swarbie an aa, is the lairgest member o the gull faimily.
A cockatoo is ony o the 21 species belangin tae the bird faimily Cacatuidae, the anly faimily in the superfaimily Cacatuoidea.
Rosmarinus officinalis, commonly kent as rosemary, is a widdy, perennial yerb wi fragrant, evergreen, needle-lik leafs an white, pink, purpie, or blae flouers, native tae the Mediterranean region.
Celery is a mairshland plant in the faimily Apiaceae that has been cultivatit as a vegetable syne antiquity.

The bar drake is a divin deuk, ane o the sawbills.
Plantago media, kent for common as lammie's lugs, is a species o flouerin plant in the plantain faimily Plantaginaceae.
The lavellan is a fairly lairge watter shrew, up tae 10 centimetres lang, wi a tail up tae three-quarters sae lang again.

The Common Garter Snake is an indigenous North American snake foond widely athort the continent.

The muir deuk or wild duck is a dabblin deuk which breeds throuoot temperate an subtropical Americae, Europe, Asie, an North Africae, an haes been introduced tae New Zealand, Australie, Peru, Brazil, Uruguay, Argentinae, Chile, the Falkland Islands an Sooth Africae.
The crab-eatin tod, forby kent as the forest tod, wid tod, an the common tod, is a livin species o medium-sized canid endemic tae the central pairt o Sooth Americae.
Przewalski's horse or Dzungarian horse, is a rare an endangered subspecies o wild horse native tae the steppes o central Asie, specifically Mongolie.
The guanaco is a camelid native tae Sooth Americae that staunds atween 1.0 an 1.2 m at the shouder an weighs aboot 90 kg.
The gaur, cried Indian bison an aw, is the lairgest extant bovine an is native tae Sooth Asie an Sootheast Asie.
The banteng, kent as tembadau an aw, is a species o wild cattle foond in Sootheast Asie.
Loose is the common name for members o the order Phthiraptera, which conteens nearly 5,000 species o weengless insect.
The Arctic wouf, forby kent as the Melville Island wouf is a possible subspecies o gray wouf native tae the Canadian Arctic Airchipelago, frae Melville Island tae Ellesmere Island.
The sheep is a quadrupedal, ruminant mammal teepically keept as fermstockin.
The annelids, kent as the ringed wirms or segmented wirms an aa, are a lairge invertebrate phylum, wi ower 17,000 modren species includin ragwirms, yirdwirms, an gells.
Sassafras is a genus o three extant an ane extinct species o deciduous trees in the faimily Lauraceae, native tae eastren North Americae an eastren Asie.
A cauf is the young o mony species o mammal.

The Grévy's zebra, forby kent as the imperial zebra, is the lairgest extant wild equid an the lairgest an maist endangered o the three species o zebra, the ither twa bein the plains zebra an the muntain zebra.
Adenosine is a purine nucleoside componed o a molecule o adenine attached tae a ribose succar molecule moiety via a β-N9-glycosidic bond.
A chemical compoond is a pure chemical substance consistin o twa or mair different chemical elements that can be separatit intae simpler substances bi chemical reactions.
Sulphuric acid is a heichly corrosive strang mineral acid wi the molecular formula H2SO4.
Adenosine triphosphate is a complex organic chemical that pairteecipates in mony processes.

Coffee is a brewed drink makkit fae roostit seeds, eften cried coffee beans, o the coffee plant.
In chemistry, a carbide is a compoond componed o carbon an a less electronegative element.
Caffeine is a bitter, white crystalline xanthine alkaloid an a stimulant drug.
Arginine is an α-amino acid.
Europium is a chemical element wi the seembol Eu an atomic nummer 63.
Zinc is a chemical element wi the seembol Zn an atomic nummer 30.
Germanium is a chemical element wi seembol Ge an atomic nummer 32.
Tellurium is a chemical element wi seembol Te an atomic nummer 52.
Calcium hydroxide, tradeetionally cried slaked lime, is an inorganic compoond wi the chemical formula Ca2.

Threonine is an α-amino acid wi the chemical formula HO2CCHCHCH3.

​ A sex organ or primary sexual characteristic, as narrowly defined, is ony anatomical pairt o the body involved in sexual reproduction an constitutin the reproductive seestem in a complex organism, especially the external sex organs. the external sex organs are an aa commonly referred tae as the genitalia or genitals.

The oxter is the pairt o the human body richt unner the jient whaur the airm jiens the shouder.

The tibia /ˈtɪbiə/, an aa kent as the shinbone or shankbane, is the lairger an stranger o the twa banes in the leg ablo the knee in vertebrates, an it connects the knee wi the ankle banes.
The frontal bane or os frontis is a bane in the human skull.
The aorta is the main artery in the human body, originatin frae the left ventricle o the hert an extendin doun tae the abdomen, whaur it splits into twao smawer arteries.
The laryngeal prominence, a featur o the human neck, is the lump or protrusion that is formed bi the angle o the thyroid cartilage surroondin the larynx.
The cerebral cortex is the cerebrum's ooter layer o neural tissue in humans an ither mammals.

The pintle is the sexual reproductive bodie pairt o the males in the ainimal families: mammals, birds, fishes, reptilians, an even insects.

In vertebrate anatomy, the pituitary gland, or hypophysis, is an endocrine gland aboot the size o a pea an weighin 0.5 gram in humans.

The fibula or cauf bane is a leg bane located on the lateral side o the tibia, wi which it is connectit abuin an ablo.
The neck is the pairt o the body, on mony terrestrial or seicontarily aquatic vertebrates, that distinguishes the heid frae the torso or trunk.

The duodenum /ˌduːəˈdinəm/ is the first section o the smaa intestine in maist heicher vertebrates, includin mammals, reptiles, an birds.

The pelvis, derived frae the Laitin wird for "basin", is an anatomical structur foond in maist vertebrates.
The endocrine seestem refers tae the collection o glands o an organism that secrete hormones directly intae the circulatory seestem tae be carried towards distant target organs.
The rectum, an aw cried the sparrel, is the feenal straicht portion o the lairge intestine in some mammals, an the gut in ithers.
In human anatomie, the thoum is the first deegit on a haund.
The maxillae are the twa maxilla banes formin the upper jaw an palate o the mooth.
In anatomy, the heid or powe o an ainimal is the rostral pairt that's for ordinar conseests o the harn, een, lugs, neb, an mooth.

The placenta is an organ that connects the developin fetus tae the uterine waw tae allae nutrient uptak, waste elimination, an gas exchynge via the mither's bluid supply, fecht against internal infection an produce hormones tae support pregnancy.

Connective tissue is ane o the fower teeps o biological tissue that support, connect, or separate different teeps o tissues an organs in the body.
A meristem is the tishie in maist plants conteenin undifferentiatit cells, foond in zones o the plant whaur growth can tak place.
In tetrapod anatomy, the sacrum is a lairge, triangular bane at the base o the spine an at the upper, back pairt o the pelvic cavity, whaur it is insertit lik a wedge atween the twa hip banes.
A reagent /riˈeɪdʒənt/ is a "substance or compoond that is addit tae a seestem in order tae bring aboot a chemical reaction, or addit tae see if a reaction occurs."
Toluene /ˈtɒluːiːn/, umwhile kent as toluol /ˈtɒluːɒl/, is a clear, watter-insoluble liquid wi the typical smell o paint thinners.
A solvent is a substance that dissolves a solute, resultin in a solution.
Risk is potential o losin something o value.
Surfactants are compoonds that lawer the surface tension atween twa liquids or atween a liquid an a solit.
Phenol, kent as carbolic acid an aw, is an aromatic organic compoond wi the molecular formula C6H5OH.
A molecule is an electrically neutral group o twa or mair atoms held thegither bi chemical bonds.
Haemoglobin, abbreviatit Hb or Hgb, is the airn-containin oxygen-transport metalloprotein in the reid bluid cells o aw vertebrates as well as the tissues o some invertebrates.
The globulins are a faimily o globular proteins that hae heicher molecular wichts nor albumins an are insoluble in pure watter but soluble in dilute saut solutions.
Collagen /ˈkɒlədʒᵻn/ is the main structural protein in the extracellular space in the various connective tissues in ainimals.
Keratin is a faimily o fibrous structural proteins.
Casein is the name for a faimily o relatit phosphoproteins.
In pheesics, thare are several kinds o dipole: An electric dipole is a separation o positive an negative charges.
Gluten is a composite o storage proteins termed prolamins an glutelins that is stored thegither wi stairch in the endosperm o various cereal grains.
In biology, histones are heichly alkaline proteins foond in eukaryotic cell nuclei that package an order the DNA into structural units cried nucleosomes.
The albumins are a faimily o globular proteins, the maist common o which are the serum albumins.
In chemistry, a radical is an atom, molecule, or ion that haes unpaired valence electrons.
An ion is an atom or molecule in which the tot nummer o electrons is nae equal tae the tot nummer o protons, givin the atom a net positive or negative electrical charge.
Proteins are lairge biological molecules, or macromolecules, consistin o ane or mair chains o amino acid residues.

An antibody, an aa kent as an immunoglobulin, is a lairge, Y-shape protein produced bi plasma cells that is uised bi the immune seestem tae identify an neutralise pathogens such as bacteria an viruses.
An allele, or allel, is ane o a nummer o alternative forms o the same gene or same genetic locus.
Isotopes are variants o a pairteecular chemical element that differ in neutron nummer, awtho aw isotopes o a gien element hae the same nummer o protons in ilk atom.
A hydroxyl is a chemical functional group containin an oxygen atom connectit bi a covalent bond tae a hydrogen atom.
In organic chemistry, functional groups are speceefic groups o atoms or bonds within molecules that are responsible for the characteristic chemical reactions o those molecules.
In crystallographie, crystal structur is a description o the ordered arrangement o atoms, ions or molecules in a crystalline material.
HyperText Markup Language is a markup leid uised tae create documents intendit tae bi accessed wae a wab brouser.
A calendar is a seestem o organizin days for social, releegious, commercial or admeenistrative purposes.
Terminology is the study o terms an thair uise.

In geometry, a coordinate seestem is a seestem which uises ane or mair nummers, or coordinates, tae uniquely determine the poseetion o a pynt or ither geometric element on a manifold such as Euclidean space.

In probability theory an stateestics, the Poisson distreebution, named efter French mathematician Siméon Denis Poisson, is a discrete probability distreebution that expresses the probability o a gien nummer o events occurrin in a fixed interval o time an/or space if thir events occur wi a kent average rate an independently o the time syne the last event.
In probability theory, the normal distreebution is a very common conteenous probability distreebution.
In pheesics, spacetime is ony mathematical model that combines space an time intae a single interwoven continuum.
The Islamic calendar, Muslim calendar or Hijri calendar is a lunar calendar consistin o 12 months in a year o 354 or 355 days.
The Julian calendar, introduced bi Julius Caesar in 46 BC, wis a reform o the Roman calendar.
The Gregorian calendar is the internationally takken ceevil calendar.
A federatit state is a territorial an constitutional commonty formin pairt of a federation.
Libido, colloquially kent as sex drive, is a person's oweraw sexual drive or desire for sexual activity.
The Oedipus complex is a concept o psychoanalytic theory.
Pleisur describes the broad class o mental states that humans an ither ainimals experience as positive, enjoyable, or worth seekin.
Economic policy refers tae the actions that govrenments tak in the economic field.
Imperialism is a teep o advocacy o empire.
An inferiority complex is a lack o sel-wirth, a doubt an uncertainty, an feelins o nae meisurin up tae staundarts.
Dreams are successions o images, ideas, emotions, an sensations that occur uisually involuntarily in the mynd during certain stages o sleep.
Lust is a feelin that haes tae dae wi ettlin efter a thing, teepically sexual but it can be ettlin efter ither things lik objecks.

Fear is an emotion induced bi a threit perceived bi leevin entities, that causes a chynge in harn an organ function an ultimately a chynge in behaviour, sic as runnin awey, hidin or freezin frae traumatic events.
Necrophilia, forby kent as necrophilism, necrolagnia, necrocoitus, necrochlesis, an thanatophilia, is a sexual attraction or sexual act involvin corpse.
Emotion is, in everyday speech, a person's state o mind an instinctive responses, but scienteefic discoorse has drifted tae ither meanins an thare is no consensus on a defineetion.

Sadness is emotional pain associatit wi, or characterised bi feelins o disadvantage, loss, despair, helplessness, disappyntment an sorrae.
A biopsy is a medical test commonly performed bi a surgeon, interventional radiologist, or an interventional cardiologist involvin samplin o cells or tissues for examination.
A cult o personality arises when an individual uises mass media, propaganda, or ither methods, tae create an idealized an heroic public image, aften through unquestionin flattery an praise.
Sicht is ane o the senses.
Inductive raisonin is a method o raisonin in thatthe premises are viewed as supplyin some evidence for the truth o the conclusion. this is in contrast tae deductive raisonin.
Credit (frae Laitin credere translation.
The New Deal wis a series o domestic programs enacted in the Unitit States atween 1933 an 1938, an a few that came later.
Fashion is a popular style or practice, especially in cleidin, fitwear, accessories, makeup, bouk, or furnitur.

In economics, pertectionism is the economic policy o restrainin trade atween kintras throu methods such as tariffs on importit guids, restrictive quotas, an a variety o ither govrenment regulations designed tae allae fair competeetion atween imports an guids an services produced domestically.

Drinks, or beverages, are liquids specifically prepared for human consumption.
Feldspars are a group o rock-furmin tectosilicate meenerals that mak up as much as 60% o the Yird's crust.
Garnets /ˈɡɑːrnət/ are a group o silicate meenerals that hae been uised syne the Bronze Age as gemstanes an abrasives.
A vitamin is an organic compoond an a vital nutrient that an organism requires in leemitit amoonts.
A spice is a dried seed, fruit, ruit, baurk, or vegetable substance primarily uised for flavourin, colourin or preservin fuid.
Citrus is a common term an genus o flouering plants in the rue faimily, Rutaceae.

Penicillin is a group o antibiotics derived frae Penicillium fungi, includin penicillin G, procaine penicillin, benzathine penicillin, an penicillin V. Penicillin antibiotics are historically signeeficant acause thay are the first drugs that wur effective against mony previously serious diseases, such as syphilis, an infections caused bi staphylococci an streptococci.
A bean is a seed o ane o several genera o the flouerin plant faimily Fabaceae, that are uised for human or ainimal fuid.
Aluminium oxide is a chemical compoond o aluminium an oxygen wi the chemical formula Template:Aluminium2O3.
The mica group o sheet silicate minerals includes several closely relatit materials havin close tae perfect basal cleavage.
The plastid is a major dooble-membrane organelle foond, amang ithers, in the cells o plants an algae.
A nutrient is a chemical that an organism needs tae live an grow or a substance uised in an organism's metabolism which must be taken in frae its environment.
A vitamin is an organic compoond an a vital nutrient that an organism requires in leemitit amoonts.
Sodium chloride, forby kent as saut, common saut, table saut or halite, is an ionic compound wi the formula NaCl, representin equal proportions o sodium an chlorine.
Baucon is a meat product prepared frae a pig an uisually cured.
Lasagne are wide, flat-shaped pasta, an possibly ane o the auldest teeps o pasta.

In cuisine, an omelette is a dish made frae beaten eggs quickly cuiked wi butter or ile in a fryin pan, sometimes foldit aroond a fillin such as cheese, vegetables, meat, or some combination o the abuin.
Ultramarine is a deep blue colour an a pigment which wis oreeginally made bi grindin lapis lazuli intae a pouder.
Oranger juice is a juice made frae orangers.
Taffee is a confection made bi caramelisin succar or traicle alang wi butter, an occasionally floor.
Tofu, an aa kent as bean curd, is a fuid made bi coagulating soy milk an then pressin the resultin curds intae saft white blocks.
The lychee is the sole member o the genus Litchi in the soapberry faimily, Sapindaceae.
Chutney is a side dish in the cuisines o the Indian subcontinent.
Ghee is a cless o clarified butter that oreeginatit in auncient Indie an is commonly uised in Sooth Asian cuisines, tradeetional medicine, an releegious rituals.
Fother is ony agricultural fuidstuff particular fode tae domesticatit fermstockin, sic as kye, gaits, sheep, horse, chickens an pigs.
Coca-Cola, kent as Coke an aw, is a carbonatit, sweetened saft drink that is selt in maist kintras, an is the warld's best-sellin saft drink.
Propane is a three-caurbon alkane wi the molecular formula C3H8, normally a gas, but compressible tae a transportable liquid.
Biotite is a common phyllosilicate meeneral athin the mica group, wi the approximate chemical formula K3AlSi3O102.
Applejack is a strang aiple-flavoured alcoholic drink produced frae aiples, popular in the American colonial period.
Brandy is a spirit produced bi distillin wine.
A distilled beverage, spirit, liquor, or haird liquor is an alcoholic beverage produced bi distillation o a mixtur produced frae alcoholic fermentation, such as wine.
Turkis coffee is a method o preparin unfiltered coffee.
A pigment is a material that chynges the colour o reflectit or transmittit licht as the result o wavelength-selective absorption.
Seafuid is ony form o sea life regardit as fuid bi humans.
In iveryday uissage, vegetables are certain pairts o plants that are consumed bi humans as fuid as pairt o a savoury meal.
Mayonnaise, eften abbreviatit as mayo, is a Spaingie sauce, thick, creamy sauce eften uised as a condiment.
A fried egg is a cuiked dish commonly made uisin a fresh hen's egg fried whole wi minimal accompaniment.
A cappuccino, is an Italian coffee drynk which is tradeetionally prepared wi espresso, het milk, an steamed-milk faem.

Sequoiadendron giganteum is the sole livin species in the genus Sequoiadendron, an ane o three species o coniferous trees kent as reidwids, classified in the faimily Cupressaceae in the subfaimily Sequoioideae, thegither wi Sequoia sempervirens an Metasequoia glyptostroboides.
Wine is an alcoholic drink aften makkit o fermentit grape juice.
Black tea is a teep o tea that is mair oxidized nor oolong, green an white teas.
Floor is victual that hae been haselt an grund intae pouder.
Freshwatter fish
Sea fish The names o fish waled for teetles is mair tae sinder ae fish frae anither nor tae threap that is the richt ane.
Breid is a staple fuid makkit by bakin a daich o floor an watter.
Roquefort is a sheep milk cheese frae the sooth o Fraunce, an thegither wi Gorgonzola, Bleu d'Auvergne, Danablu an Stilton is ane o the warld's best kent blue cheeses.
A fish supper is battert an fried fish etten wi chips.
Guar gum, cried guaran an aw, is a galactomannan.
Ice cream is a frozen dessert uisually made frae dairy products, sic as milk an cream an eften combined wi fruits or ither ingredients an flavours.
The aiple tree is a deciduous tree in the rose faimily best kent for its sweet, pomaceous fruit, the aiple.
Fossil fuels is fuels formed bi naitural processes lik anaerobic decomposeetion o buried deid organisms.
A plastic material is ony o a wide range o synthetic or semi-synthetic organic solids that are mauldable.
The martini is a cocktail made wi gin an vermouth, an gairnished wi an olive or a leemon twist.
A pretzel is a type o baked breid product made frae daich maist commonly shaped intae a knot.
Malt is germinatit cereal grains that hae been dried in a process kent as "mautin".
Hey is gress, legumes, or ither yerbaceous plants that hae been cut, dried, an stored for uise as ainimal fother, pairteecularly for grazin ainimals such as kye, horse, gaits, an sheep.
Cognac, named efter the toun o Cognac in Fraunce, is a variety o brandy.
A pitaya /pᵻˈtaɪ.ə/ or pitahaya /ˌpɪtəˈhaɪ.ə/ is the fruit o several cactus species.
Sausage is a wey tae mak meat. fowk pit meat an spices intae wee pokes an then fry the pokes that's cried sausages.
Melatonin, chemically N-acetyl-5-methoxy tryptamine, is a hormone foond in animals, plants, fungi an bacteria in anticipation o the daily onset o darkness.
The prostaglandins are a group o physiologically active lipid compoonds havin diverse hormone-lik effects in ainimals.
A tuna is a saltwatter finfish that belangs tae the tribe Thunnini, a sub-groupin o the mackerel faimily – which thegither wi the tunas, an aa includes the bonitos, mackerels, an Spainyie mackerels.
Melanin /ˈmɛlənɪn/ is a broad term for a group o naitural pigments foond in maist organisms.
Gorgonzola is a veined Italian blue cheese, made frae unskimmed cou's milk.
Pizza is an oven-baked, flat, roond breid teepically topped wi a tomatae sauce, cheese an various toppins.
Sake or saké is an alcoholic beverage o Japanese oreegin that is made frae fermentit rice.
The neep, aiblins mair correctly the Swade neep
Emmental
Urine is a liquid bi-product o the body secretit bi the kidneys throu a process cried urination an excretit throu the urethra.
Soup is a primarily liquid fuid, generally served warm, that is made bi combinin ingredients such as meat an vegetables wi stock, juice, watter, or anither liquid.
Broth is a meal made o watter in whilk bones, bridie, or vegetables hae bin simmered, wi beef or wee lamb fur example.
Sequoia sempervirens is the sole livin species o the genus Sequoia in the cypress faimily Cupressaceae.
An axon, kent as a nerve feebre an aw, is a lang, slender projection o a nerve cell, or neuron, that teepically conducts electrical impulses away frae the neuron's cell body.
Het chocolate, is a drink made o milk, chocolate an succar.
Whisky is an alcoholic drink distillt frae grain, aften includin maut, that haes than been aged in widden baurrels.
Cake is a fairm o breid or breid-lik fuid.
Chocolate is a sweet tastin fuid, made frae cocoa beans.
Mead is an alcoholic beverage creatit bi fermentin honey wi watter, sometimes wi various fruits, spices, grains, or hops.
Cheesecake is a sweet dish conseestin primarily o a mixtur o saft, fresh cheese, eggs, an succar. eften on a crust or base made frae grushed cuikies or graham crackers, pastry or spoonge cake.

Androgen, an aa cried androgenic hormone or testoid, is ony naitural or synthetic compound, uisually a steroid hormone, that stimulates or controls the development an maintenance of male characteristics in vertebrates bi bindin tae androgen receptors.
In geology, a rock is a naiturally occurrin solit aggregate o ane or mair meenerals or meeneraloids.
Aitmeal is a teep o coorse floor made o hulled ait grains that hae aither been milled, steel-cut, or rowed.
Venison is the meat o a gemme ainimal, especially a deer.
Pork is the culinar name for meat frae the domestic pig.
Beef is the culinary name for meat frae bovines, especially kye.

Tequila is a regional specific name for a distilled beverage made frae the blue agave plant, primarily in the aurie surroondin the ceety o Tequila, 65 km northwast o Guadalajara, an in the hielands o the central wastren Mexican state o Jalisco.
Mozzarella is a cheese, oreeginally frae soothren Italy, tradeetionally made frae Italian buffalo an later cou's milk bi the pasta filata method.
Milk is a white liquid produced bi the mammary glands o mammals.
Semolina is the coarse, purified wheat middlings o durum wheat uised in makin pasta, breakfast cereals, puddins, an couscous.
A saft drink is a beverage that teepically contains carbonatit watter, a sweetener an a flavourin.
Nougat is a faimily o confectioneries made wi succar an/or honey, roastit nuts, whipped egg whites, an sometimes chopped candied fruit.
Butane is an organic compoond wi the formula C4H10 that is an alkane wi fower carbon atoms.
Gabbro /ˈɡæbroʊ/ refers tae a lairge group o dark, eften phaneritic, mafic intrusive igneous rocks chemically equivalent tae plutonic basalt.
Ace is an auld tairm for the ane on a die, gaun back tae the 17t centurie.
Eggs are laid bi female ainimals o mony different species, includin birds, reptiles, amphibians, an fish, an hae been eaten bi humans for thoosands o years.

Papyrus /pəˈpaɪrəs/ is a thin paper-lik material made frae the pith o the papyrus plant, Cyperus papyrus, a wetland sedge that wis ance abundant in the Sudd o Soothren Sudan alang wi the Nile Delta o Egyp.
Peat, cried turf or truff an aw, is an accumulation o pairtially decayed vegetation or organic matter that is unique tae naitural auries cried peatlands, bogs, mires, muirs, or muskegs.
Macaroni is a variety o dry pasta in the shape o narrae tubes, oreeginatin frae Italy, made wi durum wheat, uisually wioot egg.
Pepsi-Cola, is a weel-likit cola, a carbonatit saft drink makkit bi PepsiCo, alang wi bein the main rival o Coca-Cola.
Chloroplasts /ˈklɔːrəplæsts/ are organelles, specialised subunits, in plant an algal cells.
Granite is a common teep o felsic intrusive igneous rock that is granular an phaneritic in textur.
Bladdoch is a baurmt dairy drink.
Pilaf is a dish in which rice is cuiked in a saisoned broth.
Risotto . Northren Italian: [riˈzɔtto]) is a north Italian rice dish cuiked in a broth tae a creamy consistency.
Baklava is a rich, sweet ottoman pastry made o layers o phyllo pastry filled wi chopped nits an sweetened wi syrup or honey.
Igneous rock is ane o the three main rock types, the ithers bein sedimentary an metamorphic rock.
Sedimentary rocks are types o rock that are formed bi the deposeetion o material at the Yird's surface an within bodies o watter.
Graivel is componed o unconsolidated rock fragments that hae a general pairticle size range an include size clesses frae granule- tae boulder-sized fragments.
A neep or tumshie is the ruit crap brassica rapa var.
Beetraw is a product o Beta vulgaris that is for ordinar etten as a ruit crap.
Sweitin, an aw kent as perspiration, is the production o fluids secretit bi the sweit glands in the skin o mammals.
Estrogen or oestrogen is the primary female sex hormone an is responsible for development an regulation o the female reproductive seestem an seicontar sex characteristics.
Pasta is a staple fuid o tradeetional Italian cuisine, wi the first reference datin tae 1154 in Sicily.

Dendrites are the branched projections o a neuron that act tae propagate the electrochemical stimulation received frae ither neural cells tae the cell body, or soma, o the neuron frae which the dendrites project.
Sauerkraut, directly translatit: "sour cabbitch", is finely cut cabbitch that haes been fermentit bi various lactic acid bacteria, includin Leuconostoc, Lactobacillus, an Pediococcus.
Cotton is a saft, fluffy staple fiber that grows in a boll, or protective capsule, aroond the seeds o cotton plants o the genus Gossypium in the faimily o Malvaceae.
Toast is sliced breid that has been brouned bi exposur tae radiant heat.
In cell biology, the centrosome is an organelle that serves as the main microtubule organisin center o the ainimal cell as well as a regulator o cell-cycle progression.
A crêpe or crepe is a teep o verra thin pancake.
Galena is the naitural mineral form o lead sulfide.
Brie is a saft cou's milk cheese named efter Brie, the French region from which it originatit.
Parritch is a dish made bi bylin grund, crushed, or chappit stairchy plants – typically grain – in watter or milk.
Ricotta is an Italian whey cheese made from sheep milk whey left ower frae the production o cheese.
A meeneral is a naiturally occurrin substance that is solid an stable at ruim temperatur, representable bi a chemical formula, uisually abiogenic, an haes an ordered atomic structur.
Claith, whiles cried fabric is an artifeecial material.
A drog is ony substance that, when inhaled, injectit, smeukit, consumed, absorbed via a patch on the skin, or dissolved unner the tongue causes a physiological chynge in the bouk.
Vinegar is a liquid consistin mainly o acetic acid an watter.
Histamine is an organic nitrogenous compoond involved in local immune responses as well as regulatin physiological function in the gut an actin as a neurotransmitter.
Chips are tatties that been cuttit intae lang pieces an fried till thay're saft.
Absinthe is historically describit as a distilled, heichly alcoholic beverage.
Gin is a spirit which derives its predominant flavour frae juneper berries.
Adobe is a biggin material made frae yird an ither organic materials.
Port wine is a Portuguese fortifee'd wine produced wi distilled grape speerits exclusively in the Douro Valley in the northern provinces o Portugal.
Skoosh can refer tae aither 1) the muivement o a liquid out o something or 2) a carbonatit saft drink or a juice, inspeciallie whan tae wi alcohol.
Oolong /uloŋ/ is a tradeetional Cheenese tea produced throu a unique process includin witherin the plant unner the strang sun an oxidation afore curlin an twistin.
Green tea is made frae the leafs frae Camellia sinensis that haes unnergaun minimal oxidation throu the processin.
A margarita is a cocktail consistin o tequila, orange liqueur, an lime juice eften served wi saut on the rim o the gless.
In geology, beryl is a meeneral componed o beryllium aluminium cyclosilicate wi the chemical formula Be3Al26.
Fur is uised in reference tae the hair o animals, uisually mammals, particularly those wi extensive body hair coverage.
Meat is ainimal flesh that is eaten as fuid.
Lime is a term referrin tae a citrus fruit which is typically roond, green, 3–6 cm in diameter, an containin sour pulp.
Wid is the xylem tissue o widden plaunts, for ordinar trees but scrogs an aw.

Ethanol /ˈɛθɑːnɒl/, an aa cried ethyl alcohol /ˈɛθɪl/, pure alcohol, grain alcohol, or drinkin alcohol, is a volatile, flammable, colourless liquid wi the structural formula CH3CH2OH, eften abbreviatit as C2H6O. A psychoactive drig an ane o the auldest recreational drigs kent, ethanol produces a state kent as alcohol intoxication whan consumed as a beverage.
Nacre an aa kent as mither o pearl, is an organic-inorganic composite material produced bi some molluscs as an inner shell layer. it is an aa whit maks up the ooter coatin o pearls.
Haematite, is the mineral form o airn oxide, ane o several airn oxides.
In cell biology, the cytoplasm is the material within a leevin cell, excludin the cell nucleus.
Whey or milk serum is the liquid remainin efter milk haes been curdled an strained.
Semen, an aa kent as seminal fluid, is an organic fluid that may contain spermatozoa.
Molasses or treacle is a viscous bi-product o the refinin o succarcane, grapes, or succar beets intae succar.

Ketchup, an aa catsup, is a table sauce, tradeetionally o various flavors, notably mushruim, oyster an wawnit, but in modren times the term wioot modification uisually means tomato ketchup, whiles cried tomato sauce, or reid sauce.
An ait cake is a flatbreid akin tae a cracker or biscuit, bit can be a pan scone an aw.
Platelets, an aa cried thrombocytes, are a component o bluid whose function is tae stap bleedin bi clumpin an clottin bluid vessel injuries.

A sandwich is a fuid item consistin o ane or mair teeps o fuid, sic as vegetables, slicit cheese or meat, placit on or atween slices o breid, or mair generally ony dish whaurin twa or mair pieces o breid serve as a conteener or wrapper for some ither fuid.
Vodka is a distilled beverage componed primarily o watter an ethanol, sometimes wi traces o impurities an flavorins.
Gelatin or gelatine is a leamin, colourless, brickle, wangustie fuid ingredient, derived frae collagen that itsel is got frae various ainimal bi-products.
Rhyolite is an igneous, volcanic rock, o felsic composeetion.
Corundum is a creestalline form o aluminium oxide teepically conteenin traces o airn, titanium, vanadium an chromium.
A croissant is a buttery flaky viennoiserie pastry named for its weel kent crescent shape.
Shortbreid is a type o biscuit tradeetionally made frae ane pairt white succar, twa pairts butter, an three pairts flour.
Emmledeug is a culinary term uised for tae refer tae the harigalds an internal organs o a butched ainimal.
Ice is watter frozen intae a solit state.
Ambergris is a solit, waxy, flammable substance o a dull grey or blackish colour produced in the digestive seestem o sperm whauls.
Monosodium glutamate is the sodium saut o glutamic acid, ane o the maist abundant naiturally occurrin non-essential amino acids.

Salt is a mineral substance componed primarily o sodium chloride, a chemical compoond belangin tae the lairger class o ionic sauts. saut in its naitural furm as a crystalline mineral is kent as rock saut or halite.
Sybaes is a edible plant o the genus Allium.
The Hoose o Bourbon is a European ryal hoose o French origin, a branch o the Capetian dynasty.
The Hoose o Hohenzollern is a dynasty o umwhile princes, electors, keengs, an emperors o Hohenzollern, Brandenburg, Proushie, the German Empire, an Romanie.
White fowk is a racial clessification specifier, uised for fowk o Europid auncestry, wi the exact implications dependent on context.
The Hoose o Habsburg, cried Hoose o Hapsburg, or Hoose o Austrick an aw, wis ane o the maist important ryal hooses o Europe.
A dynasty is a sequence o rulers frae the same faimily, uisually in the context o a feudal or monarchical seestem but sometimes an aa appearin in elective republics.
The Tudor dynasty wis a pithie European ryal hoose o Welsh origeen that ringed the Kinrick o Ingland frae 1485 till 1603.
A race is a groupin o humans based on shared pheesical or social qualities intae categories generally viewed as distinct bi society.
A faimily is whit ye caw fowk that's sib til ither bi mairiage, bi bluid or bi affection.
The Hoose o Windsor is the ryal hoose o the Unitit Kinrick an the ither Commonweel realms.
The Hoose o Lancaster wis the name o twa cadet brainches o the ryal Hoose o Plantagenet.
The Hoose o Hanover is a Germanic ryal dynasty that haes ringed ower the Duchy o Brunswick-Lüneburg, the Kinrick o Hanover an the Kinrick o Great Breetain an the Kinrick o Ireland.
The Hoose o Plantagenet wis a ryal hoose which oreeginatit frae the lands o Anjou in Fraunce.

The Hoose o Romanov wis the seicont imperial dynasty, efter the Rurik dynasty, tae rule ower Roushie, which reigned frae 1613 till the abdication o Emperor Nicholas II on Mairch 15, 1917, as a result o the Februar Revolution.
In Greek meethology, Styx is a deity an a river that forms the boondary atween Yird an the Unnerwarld.

Atlantis is a feectional island mentioned within an allegory on the hubris o naitions in Plato's warks Timaeus an Critias, whaur it represents the antagonist naval pouer that besieges "Auncient Athens", the pseudo-historic embodiment o Plato's ideal state in The Republic.
Pangaea or Pangea wis a supercontinent that exeestit during the late Paleozoic an early Mesozoic eras.
Borneo is the third-lairgest island in the warld an the lairgest island in Asie.

column2: ['na h-eileanan siar', 'ooter hebrides', 'the waster isles', 'eileanan siar', 'na h-eileanan an iar', 'outer hebrides', 'wastren isles', 'waster isles']
column3: The Waster or Wastren Isles, cried Ooter Hebrides an aw is an iland chain aff the wast coast o Scotland.
The Sea o Azov, kent in Classical Antiquity as Loch Maeotis, Meotida in numerous European leids a sea on the sooth o Eastren Europe.

The Bay o Fundy is a bay on the Atlantic coast o North Americae, on the northeast end o the Gulf o Maine atween the Canadian provinces o New Brunswick an Nova Scotia, wi a smaa portion touchin the U.S. state o Maine.

In baith astrology an historical astronomy, the zodiac is a circle o twelve 30° diveesions o celestial longitude that are centered upon the ecliptic, the apparent path o the Sun athort the celestial sphere ower the coorse o the year.
A loch is a muckle bit o watter athin a bit o land.
A lagoon is a shallae bouk o watter separatit frae a lairger body o watter bi barrier islands or reefs.
The Talian peninsula is a peninsula in Europe wi the maist o Italy, the hale o San Marino an the hale o the Vatican Ceety on it.
The Purus River or Rio Purús is a tributary o the Amazon River in Sooth Americae.
The Cayman Islands are a Breetish Owerseas Territory in the wastren Caribbean Sea.
Anguilla is a Breetish owerseas territory in the Caribbean.
The Mackenzie River is the lairgest an langest river seestem in Canadae, an is exceedit anly bi the Mississippi River seestem in North Americae.
The Ryukyu Islands (琉球諸島, Ryūkyū-shotō), kent in Japanese as the Nansei Islands (南西諸島, Nansei-shotō, lit.

The Mariana Islands are an arc-shaped airchipelago made up bi the summits o fifteen volcanic muntains in the north-wastren Paceefic Ocean atween the 12t an 21st parallels north an alang the 145t meridian east.
The Lesser Sunda Islands or Nusa Tenggara are a group o islands in Maritime Sootheast Asie, north o Australie.
The Sunda Islands are a group o islands in the Malay airchipelago.
The Greater Sunda Islands are a group o muckle islands within the Malay Airchipelago.
Sooth Americae's the continent locatit tae the sooth o North Americae.
The sea, the warld ocean, or simply the ocean, is the connectit bouk o sauty watter that kivers ower 70 percent o the Yird's surface.
The Don is ane o the major rivers o Roushie.

The Po is a river that flows either 652 km or 682 km – considerin the length o the Maira, a richt baunk tributary – eastward athort northren Italy, frae a spring seepin frae a stony hillside at Pian del Re, a flat place at the heid o the Val Po unner the northwast face o Monviso through a delta projectin intae the Adriatic Sea near Venice.
The Vistula is the langest an lairgest river in Poland, at 1,047 kilometres in lenth.
The Seine is a 776 km lang river an an important commercial watterway within the Paris Basin in the north o Fraunce.
The Loire is the langest river in Fraunce.
The Republic o Cheenae, commonly kent as Taiwan, is a kintra in East Asie locatit aff the east coast o mainland Cheenae.
Lemnos is an island o Greece in the northren pairt o the Aegean Sea.
The Faroe Islands or faerae Isles or Faroes is a smaw curn o islands in the Nor' Atlantic Ocean atween Scotland, Norawa an Iceland.
The Great Lochs is a collection o fresh watter lochs locate in eastren North Americae on the Canadae - Unitit States mairch.

The Tuamotus or the Tuamotu Airchipelago are a French Polynesie cheen o awmaist 80 islands an atolls, stretchin frae the northwast tae the sootheast ower an aurie o the soothren Paceefic Ocean roughly the size o Wastren Europe, wi a laund aurie o 850 square kilometres an 16,000 indwallers, formin the lairgest cheen o atolls in the warld.

The Republic o the Marshall Islands /ˈmɑrʃəl ˈaɪləndz/, is a Micronesian naition o atolls an islands in the middle o the Paceefic Ocean, juist wast o the Internaitional Date Line an juist north o the Equator.
The Gilbert Islands are a chain o saxteen atolls an coral islands in the Paceefic Ocean.

Bermuda /bɜːrˈmjuːdə/, an aa referred tae in legal documents as the Bermudas or Somers Isles, is a Breetish Owerseas Territory in the North Atlantic Ocean, locatit off the east coast o the Unitit States.
The Malay Airchipelago is the airchipelago atween mainland Sootheast Asie an Australie.
The Lesser Antilles is the name gien tae a group o islands in the Caribbean Sea.
The Bismarck Archipelago is a group o islands off the northeastren coast o New Guinea in the wastern Paceefic Ocean an is pairt o the Islands Region o Papua New Guinea.
The Antilles are an airchipelago bordered bi the Caribbean Sea tae the sooth an wast, the Gulf o Mexico tae the northwast, an the Atlantic Ocean tae the north an east.
The Greater Antilles is a groupin o the lairger islands in the Caribbean Sea. Cuba, Hispaniola, Puerto Rico, Jamaica, an the Cayman Islands.
An airchipelago, whiles cried an island group or island chain, is a chain, cluster or collection o islands.
The Hebrides is a group o islands aff the wast coast o Scotland, an in geological terms are makkit up o the auldest stane in the Breetish Isles.
The Canary Islands, kent as the Canaries an aw, is a Spaingie airchipelago locatit juist aff the northwast coast o mainland Africae, 100 km wast o the border atween Morocco an the Wastren Sahara.
The Falkland Islands are a airchipelago in the Sooth Atlantic Ocean on the Patagonie Shelf.

The Hawaiian Islands are an airchipelago o aicht major islands, several atolls, numerous smawer islets, an unnersea seamoonts in the North Paceefic Ocean, extendin some 1,500 miles frae the island o Hawaiʻi in the sooth tae northrenmaist Kure Atoll.
The Samoan Islands are an airchipelago coverin 3,030 km2 in the central Sooth Paceefic, formin pairt o Polynesie an the wider region o Oceanie.
The Gulf o Guinea is the northeastrenmaist pairt o the tropical Atlantic Ocean atween Cape Lopez in Gabon, north an wast tae Cape Palmas in Liberie.
The Black Forest is a great forested moontain range in the state o Baden-Württemberg in soothwastren Germany.
Saba is a Caribbean isle an the smawest municipality o the Netherlands.

Hail is sib tae rain, cep it is makkit o frost.

Electromagnetic radiation is ane o the fundamental phenomena o electromagnetism, behavin as waves propagatin through space, an an aa as photon pairticles travelin through space, carryin radiant energy.
Ultraviolet licht is an electromagnetic radiation wi a wavelength frae 400 nm tae 100 nm, shorter than that o veesible licht but langer nor X-rays.
Radioactive decay, cried nuclear decay or radioactivity an aa, is the process bi whilk a nucleus o an unstable atom loses virr bi ootpittin pairticles o ionisin radiation.

​ Sexual reproduction is a form o reproduction whaur twa morphologically distinct teeps o specialized reproductive cells cried gametes fuse thegither, involvin a female's muckle ovum an a male's smawer sperm.

Asexual reproduction is a teep o reproduction bi which offspring arise frae a single organism, an inherit the genes o that parent anly. it daes nae involve the fusion o gametes an awmaist never chynges the nummer o chromosomes.

column3: Human sexual activity, human sexual practice ir human sexual behaviour is the mainer in whilk humans experience an express thair sexuality.
Bisexuality refers tae sexual cairy-on wi or pheesical attraction tae baith sexes, or a bisexual orientation.
An yirdquauk is the result o a suddent release o energie in the Yird's crust that creates seismic waves.
Agein is the process o acomin aulder.
Economic growth is the increase in the mercat value o the guids an services produced bi an economy ower time.
Photosynthesis is a process uised bi plants an ither organisms tae convert licht energy, normally frae the sun, intae chemical energy that can be uised tae fuel the organisms' activities.
Eatin is the ingestion o fuid, teepically to provide a heterotrophic organism wi energy an tae allou for growthe.
Drinkin is the act o ingeestin watter or ither liquids intae the bouk throu the mooth.
A coch is a sudden an eften repetitively occurrin, pertective reflex, which helps tae clear the lairge breathin passages frae fluids, irritants, foreign pairticles an microbes.
Sexual intercoorse, or coitus or copulation, is principally the insertion an thrustin o the penis, uisually when erect, intae the vagina for sexual pleisur, reproduction, or baith.
​Reproduction is the biological process bi which new individual organisms – "offspring" – are produced frae thair "parents".

Parallax is a displacement or difference in the apparent poseetion o an object viewed alang twa different lines o sicht, an is measured bi the angle or semi-angle o inclination atween those twa lines.
Heredity is the passin o traits tae offspring frae its parents or auncestor.
Excretion is the process bi which waste products o metabolism an ither non-uisefu materials are eliminatit frae an organism.
Refraction is the chynge in direction o a wave due tae a chynge in its transmission medium.
Voltage is the term uised for tae descrive the amoont o electrical scowth applee'd tae an electrical circuit.
In classical electromagnetism, the electric potential at a pynt o space is the amoont o electric potential energy that a unitary pynt charge would hae when locatit at that pynt.

Superconductivity is a phenomenon o exactly zero electrical reseestance an expulsion o magnetic flux fields occurrin in certain materials, cried superconductors, whan cuiled ablo a chairacteristic creetical temperatur.
​ Ejaculation is the dischairge o semen frae the male reproductory tract, uisually accompanied bi orgasm.
Defecation is the final act o digestion, bi which organisms eliminate solit, semisolit, an/or liquid waste material frae the digestive tract via the anus.
Transpiration is the process o watter muivement throu a plant an its evaporation frae aerial pairts, sic as leafs, stems an flouers.
In meteorology, precipitation is ony product o the condensation o atmospheric watter vapour that faws unner gravity.
Pressur is the force applee'd perpendicular tae the surface o an object per unit aurie ower which that force is distributit.

Newton's law o universal gravitation states that ony twa bodies in the universe attract ilk ither wi a force that is directly proportional tae the product o thair masses an inversely proportional tae the square o the distance atween them.
Continental drift is the movement o the Yird's continents relative tae each ither bi appearin tae drift athort the ocean bed.
Heat capacity or thermal capacity is a meisurable pheesical quantity equal tae the ratio o the heat addit tae an object tae the resultin temperatur cheenge.
Necrosis is a form o cell injury which results in the prematur daith o cells in livin tissue bi autolysis.
A magnetosphere is the region o space surroondin an astronomical object in that chairged pairticles are manipulatit or affectit bi that object's magnetic field.

Metamorphosis is a biological process bi which an animal pheesically develops efter birth or hatchin, involvin a conspicuous an relatively abrupt chynge in the animal's body structur throu cell growth an differentiation.
In pheesics, the kinetic energy o an object is the energy which it possesses due tae its motion.
In pheesics, potential energy is energy stored in a seestem o forcefully interactin pheesical entities.
Erosion is the process bi which soil an rock are removed frae the Yird's surface bi exogenetic processes such as wind or watter flow, an then transported an deposited in ither locations.
Wather tells us whit's gaun on in the lift abuin us.
Electrophoresis is the motion o dispersed particles relative tae a fluid unner the influence o a spatially uniform electric field.

Life is a characteristic distinguishin objects havin signalin an self-sustainin processes frae those that dae nae, either acause such functions hae ceased, or acause thay lack such functions an are classified as inanimate.
Digeestion is the breakdown o muckle insoluble fuid molecules intae smaa watter-soluble fuid molecules sae that thay can be absorbed intae the wattery bluid plasma.
Metabolism is the set o life-sustainin chemical transformations within the cells o livin organisms.
Reflection is the chynge in direction o a wavefront at an interface atween twa different media sae that the wavefront returns intae the medium frae which it originatit.
Allotropy or allotropism is the property o some chemical elements tae exeest in twa or mair different forms, in the same pheesical state, kent as allotropes o thir elements.
Hydro-power or watter pouer is pouer derived frae the energy o fallin watter an runnin watter, which mey be harnessed for uisefu purposes.
Bluid pressur is the pressur exertit bi circulatin bluid upon the waws o bluid vessels.
Cell diveesion is the process bi which a parent cell divides intae twa or mair dauchter cells.
Distillation' is a process o separatin the component substances frae a liquid mixtur bi selective evaporation an condensation.
Condensation is the chynge o the pheesical state o matter frae gas phase intae liquid phase, an is the reverse o vaporization.
Fire is a phenomenon o combustion kyth'd in strang heat an licht in the furm o a lowe or flames.
Coagulation is the process bi which bluid chynges frae a liquid tae a gel, formin a clot.
Birth, forby kent as hame-comin, is the act or process o bearin or bringin forth affspring.
Ionisation is the process bi that an atom or a molecule acquires a negative or positive chairge bi gainin or losin electrons.
Sweitin, an aw kent as perspiration, is the production o fluids secretit bi the sweit glands in the skin o mammals.
Lacrimation, or lachrymation, is the secretion o tears, which eften serves tae clean an lubricate the een in response tae an irritation o the een.
Germination is the process bi that a plant growes frae a seed.
Electric pouer is the rate at which electric energy is transferred bi an electric circuit.
Electric chairge is the physical property o maiter that causes it tae experience a force whan close tae ither electrically chairged maiter.
Electromotive force, cried emf an aw, is the voltage developed bi ony soorce o electrical energy sic as a battery or dynamo.
Sunlicht is a portion o the electromagnetic radiation gien off bi the Sun, in pairteecular infrareid, veesible, an ultraviolet licht.
Freection is the force resistin the relative motion o solit surfaces, fluid layers, an material elements slidin against ilk ither.
A fluid is an owerflow o watter that submerges laund which is uisually dry.
Evolution is chynge in heritable traits o biological populations ower successive generations.
A field is a pheesical quantity that haes a value for ilka pynt in space an time.
Metastasis, or metastatic disease, is the spread o a cancer or ither disease frae ane organ or pairt tae anither nae directly connectit wi it.
Liquid is ane o the fower fundamental states o matter, an is the anly state wi a definite volume but no fixed shape.
Solit is ane o the fower fundamental states o matter.
Gas is ane o the fower fundamental states o matter.
Convection is the concertit, collective movement o groups or aggregates o molecules within fluids an rheids, aither throu advection or throu diffusion or as a combination o baith o them.
Thermal conduction is the transfer o heat bi microscopic collisions o pairticles an muivement o electrons within a bouk.
Rain is a kynd o precipitation, ither o whilk includes snaw, sleet, hail, an dyow.
Dew, whiles spelt dyow, is smaw dribs o watter that gits on thin objects in the aerlie mornin or e'en endue tae condesation.
A comet is an icy smaw Solar Seestem bouk that, when passin close tae the Sun, heats up an begins tae ootgas, displayin a veesible atmosphere or coma, an sometimes an aa a tail.
A pairticle is a minute fragment or quantity o matter.

Gluons /ˈɡluːɒnz/ are elementary pairticles that act as the exchynge pairticles for the strang force atween quarks, analogous tae the exchynge o photons in the electromagnetic force atween twa charged pairticles.
Beta pairticles are heich-energy, heich-speed electrons or positrons emittit bi certaint teeps o radioactive nuclei sic as potassium-40.
The tau, an aa cried the tau lepton, tau pairticle or tauon, is an elementary pairticle seemilar tae the electron, wi negative electric charge an a spin o 1⁄2.
In pairticle pheesics, a pion is ony o three subatomic pairticles: π0, π+, an π−.
A shot starn is whit is seen whan a space rock faws tae Yird.
In pairticle pheesics, a gauge boson is a force carrier, a bosonic pairticle that carries ony o the fundamental interactions o naitur.
A terrestrial planet, telluric planet or rocky planet is a planet that is componed primarily o silicate rocks or metals.
Alpha pairticles consist o twa protons an twa neutrons boond thegither intae a pairticle identical tae a helium nucleus.
A photon is an elementary pairticle, the quantum o licht an aw ither furms o electromagnetic radiation, an the force carrier for the electromagnetic force, even when static via virtual photons.
The Crab Nebula is a supernova remnant an pulsar wind nebula in the constellation o Taurus.
A reid dwarf is a smaa an relatively cuil starn on the main sequence, either late K or M spectral type.
A supernova is a stellar explosion that is mair energetic nor a nova.
A neutron starn is a teep o compact starn that can result frae the gravitational collapse o a massive starn efter a supernova.
A chromosome is a DNA molecule wi pairt or aw o the genetic material o an organism.
In pairticle pheesics, mesons are hadronic subatomic pairticles componed o ane quark an ane antiquark, bound thegither bi the strang interaction.
A lepton is an elementary, spin-​1⁄2 pairticle that daes nae unnergo strang interactions, but is subject tae the Pauli exclusion principle.
The neutron is a subatomic hadron pairticle that haes the seembol Error no symbol defined or Error no symbol defined, na net electric charge an a mass slichtly lairger nor that o a proton.
The muon is an elementary pairticle seemilar tae the electron, wi unitary negative electric charge o roughly −1 an a spin o 1⁄2, but wi much mair mass.
The electron is a subatomic particle wi a negative elementary electric charge.
The positron or antielectron is the antipairticle or the antimatter coonterpairt o the electron.
A neutrino is an electrically neutral, weakly interactin elementary subatomic pairticle wi hauf-integer spin.
In pairticle pheesics, a hadron /ˈhædrɒn/ is a composite pairticle made o quarks held thegither bi the strang force.
The Muin is an astronomical bouk that orbits planet Yird, bein Yird's anerly permanent naitural satellite.
Asteroids are minor planets, especially those o the inner Solar Seestem.
A baryon is a composite subatomic pairticle made up o three quarks.
In pairticle pheesics, a fermion is ony subatomic pairticle chairacterised bi Fermi–Dirac stateestics.
The Universe is commonly defined as the totality o existence, includin planets, starns, galaxies, the contents o intergalactic space, the smawest subatomic pairticles, an aw matter an energy.
Algol, kent colloquially as the Demon Starn, is a bricht starn in the constellation Perseus.
Yird, itherwise kent as the Warld or the Globe, is the third planet frae the Sun an the anerly object in the universe kent tae herbour life.
Arcturus o the constellation Boötes is the brichtest starn in the northren celestial hemisphere.
Maurs is the fowert planet frae the Sun in the Solar system.
Vesta, minor-planet designation 4 Vesta, is ane o the lairgest asteroids in the Solar Seestem, wi a mean diameter o 525 kilometre.
Antares is a reid supergiant starn in the Milky Way galaxy an the saxteent brichtest starn in the nichttime sky.
Aldebaran /ælˈdɛbərən/ is a reid giant starn locatit aboot 68 licht years awa in the zodiac constellation o Taurus.
Vega is the brichtest starn in the constellation Lyra, the fift brichtest starn in the nicht sky an the seicont brichtest starn in the northren celestial hemisphere, efter Arcturus.
Sirius is the brichtest starn in the Yird's nicht sky.
Spica is the brichtest starn in the constellation Virgo, an the 15t brightest starn in the nicht sky.
Ceres /ˈsɪəriːz/ is the lairgest object in the asteroid belt, which lies atween the orbits o Maurs an Jupiter.
Proxima Centauri is a reid dwarf aboot 4.24 licht-years frae the Sun, inside the G-clood, in the constellation o Centaurus.
The Y chromosome is ane o twa sex chromosomes in mammals, includin humans, an mony ither ainimals.
The X chromosome is ane o the twa sex-determinin chromosomes in mony ainimal species, includin mammals, an is foond in baith males an females.
Mercur is the smawest an closest tae the Sun o the aicht planets in the Solar Seestem, wi an orbital period o aboot 88 Yird days.

A central processin unit is the haurdware within a computer that cairies oot the instructions o a computer program bi performin the basic arithmetical, logical, an input/ootput operations o the seestem.
A tumulus is a moond o yird an stanes raised ower a grave or graves.
An airch is a structur that spans a space an supports structur an wecht abuin it.
A boomerang is a tuil, teepically constructit as a flat air foil that, when thrawn, is designed tae spin aboot an axis perpendicular tae the direction o its flicht.
A bicycle, eften cried a bike, is a human-pouered, pedal-driven, single-track vehicle, haein twa wheels attached tae a frame, ane ahint the ither.

A computer network or data network is a telecommunications network that allaes computers tae exchynge data.
A modem is a device that modulates an analog carrier signal tae encode deegital information and demodulates the signal tae decode the transmittit information.
Telecommunication is communication at a distance bi technological means, particularly through electrical signals or electromagnetic waves.
The tawse wis an implement uised for corporal punishment.
Breeks or troosers are an item o claes worn on the nether pairt o the body, kiverin baith shanks separately.
An automobile or motor is a wheeled motor vehicle for transportin passengers, that cairies its ain ingine or motor an aw.

A dam is a barrier that impoonds watter or unnergrund streams.
A fence is a freestaundin structur designed tae restrict or prevent movement athort a boondary.
A Twilt is a kynd o beddin— a bed kiverin makkit o a twiltit tap, a layer o battin, an a layer o fabric for backin, for ordinar soudert thegither uisin the technique o twiltin.
Syne 1815, steamers wis a graund wey o gaun aboot doun the River Clyde an aw aboot the Firth o Clyde an aroond the coasts an islands o Scotland.
A ferry is a merchant vessel uised tae carry passengers, an sometimes vehicles an cargo as well, athort a bouk o watter.
A trumpet is a muisical instrument.
In local govrenment, a ceety haw, toun house, civic centre, a guildhaw, or a municipal biggin, is the chief admeenistrative biggin o a ceety toun or ither municipality.
In local govrenment, a ceety haw, toun house, civic centre, a guildhaw, or a municipal biggin, is the chief admeenistrative biggin o a ceety toun or ither municipality.

A preeson kent as the Jyle, the kittie or the towbuith an aw, is a place that fowk is pheesically confined an, uisually, deprived o a reenge o personal freedoms.
A bordel is a place whaur fowk engage in sexual acteevity wi prostitutes.
A hottle is an establishment that provides peyed ludgin on a short-term basis.
A tram is a rail vehicle which runs on tracks along public urban streets, an whiles on a segregatit richt o way forby.

The Compact Cassette or Musicassette, an aa commonly cried cassette tape, audio cassette, or simply tape or cassette, is a magnetic tape recordin format for audio recordin an playback released bi Philips in 1962.
A solar cell, or photovoltaic cell, is an electrical device that converts the energy o licht directly intae electricity bi the photovoltaic effect.
The teddy beir is a saft toy in the form o a beir.
An abbey, or aibey, is a Catholic, Anglican, or Orthodox Christian monastery or convent.
In chemistry, saip is a saut o a fatty acid.
A sock is an item o cleidin worn on the feet an eften coverin the ankle an some pairt o the cauf.

A tap is a toy designed tae spin rapidly on the grund, the motion o which causes it tae remeen precisely balanced on its tip acause o its rotational inertia.

A swuird is a lang and nairae metal object connectit tae a haundle.
A newspaper is a periodical publication containin news, ither informative airticles, an uisually adverteesin.

A museum is an institution that cares for a collection o airtifacts an ither objects o airteestic, cultural, heestorical, or scienteefic importance an maks them available for public viewin throu exhibits that mey be permanent or temporary.

A parachute is a device uised tae slow the motion o an object through an atmosphere bi creatin drag, or in the case o ram-air parachutes, aerodynamic lift.

A yett is a pheesical hinderance that can be opent or closed for tae hinder or allou fowk or craiturs tae gang intae or oot o a space inby waws, or a fence, or thay micht be juist decorative.

A shotgun is a fireairm that is uisually designed tae be fired frae the shouder, that uises the energy o a fixed shell tae fire a nummer o smaw spherical pellets cried shot, or a solit projectile cried a slug.
A soummin puil, soummin bath, wadin puil, or paddlin puil is a container that is filled wi watter tae enable soummin or ither leisur activities.
