The sabre is a swuird that uisually haes a curved, single-edged blade an a rather lairge haund guard, coverin the knuckles o the haund as well as the thumb an forefinger.

The Kamikaze, offeecially Tokubetsu Kōgekitai, abbreviatit as Tokkō Tai, an uised as a verb as Tokkō, war suicide attacks bi militar aviators frae the Empire o Japan against Allied naval vessels in the closin stages o the Paceefic campaign o Warld War II, designed tae destroy warships mair effectively than wis possible wi conventional attacks.
A sauna is a smaw chaumer or hoose designed as a place tae expairience dry or weet heat sessions, or an estaiblishment wi ane or mair o thir an auxiliar faceelities.
The Pentagon is the heidquarters o the Unitit States Depairtment o Defense, locatit in Arlington Coonty, Virginie.

The Great Waw o Cheenae is a series o fortifications made o stane, brick, tamped yird, firth, an ither materials, generally biggit alang an east-tae-wast line athort the historical northren borders o Cheenae in pairt tae pertect the Cheenese Empire or its prototeepical states agin intrusions bi various nomadic groups or militar incursions bi various warlike fowks or forces.

A windae is an openin in a waw o a biggin, in a caur etc., fur tae let air an licht in.
The sporran, a tradeetional pairt o male Scots Hieland dress, is a pootch worn on a kilt.
A sark is a kynd o claes that is makkit tae kiver the breest.

A Sari, saree, sadi, or shari is a Sooth Asian female garment that consists o a drape varyin frae 4.5 metres tae 8 metres in lenth an 60 cm tae 1.20 m in breadth that is teepically wrapped aroond the waist, wi ane end draped ower the shouder, barin the midriff.
Unnergarments are items o cleidin worn beneath ooter claithes, uisually in direct contact wi the skin, althou thay mey comprise mair nor a single layer.
A warship is a naval ship that is biggit an primarily intendit for naval warfare.
A haimer is a tuil that delivers a blow tae an object.
A mobile phone is a device that can mak an receive telephone caws ower a radio link while movin aroond a wide geographic aurie.
A gavelock is a tuil conseestin o a metal baur wi a single curved end an flattened pynts, aften wi a smaw fissure on ane or baith ends for remuivin nails.
A pick is a hand tuil wi a haird heid attached perpendicular tae the handle.
A fechter aircraft is a militar aircraft designed primarily for air-tae-air combat against ither aircraft, as opponed tae bombers an attack aircraft, whase main mission is tae attack grund targets.

A corvette is a smaa, maneuverable, lichtly airmed warship, oreeginally smawer nor a frigate an lairger nor a coastal patrol craft or fast attack craft, altho mony recent designs resemble frigates in size an role.
A washin machine is a machine uised tae wash laundry, such as cleidin an sheets.
A synagogue, an aa spelled synagog is a Jewish hoose o prayer.

A refrigerator is a cuilin appliance makkit up o a thermally insulatit compairtment an a mechanism for tae transpose heat frae it tae the environs athoot, cuilin the contents tae a temperatur ablo ruim temperatur.
A kilt is a ceremonial airticle o claes worn in Scotland.
A bayonet is a knife, swuird, or spike-shaped weapon designed tae fit in, on, ower or unnerneath the muzzle o a rifle, musket or seemilar weapon, turnin the gun intae a spear.
A pier is a raised structure, includin bridge an buildin supports an walkways, ower watter, teepically supportit bi widely spread piles or pillars.
Solar panel refers either tae a photovoltaic module, a solar het watter panel, or tae a set o solar photovoltaic modules electrically connectit an moontit on a supportin structur.
A castle is a muckle biggin that wis biggit tae pertect the keeng or laird an his faimlie that bides thare.
Hoover Dam, ance kent as Boulder Dam, is a concrete arch-gravity dam in the Black Canyon o the Colorado River, on the border atween the U.S. states o Nevada an Arizona.
A cruiser is a teepe o warship.
A machete is a muckle cleaver-lik knife.
Timpani, or kettledrums, are muisical instruments in the percussion faimily.
The Statue o Liberty is a colossal neoclassical sculpture on Liberty Island in New York Harbor, designed bi Frédéric Bartholdi an dedicatit on October 28, 1886.
A kil is a chaumer that is thermally insulate.
A Zeppelin wis a teep o rigid airship named efter the German Coont Ferdinand von Zeppelin who pioneered rigid airship development at the beginnin o the 20t century.
A supermercat, a muckle form o the tradeetional grocery store, is a sel-service shop offerin a wide variety o fuid an hoosehauld products, organised intae aisles.

A gailey is a teep o ship propelled bi rowers that oreeginatit in the eastren Mediterranean Sea an wis uised for warfare, trade an piracy frae the first millennium BC. Galleys dominatit naval warfare in the Mediterranean frae the 8t century BC till development o advanced sailin warships in the 17t century.

A modren stadium is a place or venue for ootduir sports, concerts, or ither events an consists o a field or stage either pairtly or completely surroondit bi a structur designed tae allae spectators tae stand or sit an view the event.
A arena is a enclosed aurie, aften circular or oval-shaped, designed tae showcase theatre, muisical performances, or sportin events.
An aircraft carrier is a warship that serves as a seagangin airbase, equipped wi a full-lenth flicht deck an facilities for carryin, armin, deployin, an recoverin aircraft.
A joystick is an input device consistin o a stick that pivots on a base an reports its angle or direction tae the device it is controllin.
An umberellae is a canopie makkit tae fend agin onfaw or sunlicht.
A train is a connectit bunch o vehicles made tae be hurlin on train racks for tae tranport passengers or frauchts.

The mitre, an aa spelled miter, is a teep o heidgear nou kent as the tradeetional, ceremonial heid-dress o bishops an certain abbots in tradeetional Christianity. continuin the priestly practice o Temple Judaism.
A local aurie network is a computer network that interconnects computers athin a leemitit aurie, for insample, a hame, schuil, computer laboratory, or office biggin uisin network media.
A diesel locomotive is a teep o railwey locomotive in which the prime mover is a diesel ingine.

A modren torpedo is a sel-propelled wappen wi an explosive warheid, launched abuin or ablo the watter surface, propelled unnerwattter taewart a target, an designed tae detonate aither on contact wi its target or in proximity tae it.
Bobsleigh or bobsled is a winter sport in which teams o twa or fower mak timed runs doun narrow, twistin, banked, iced tracks in a gravity-pouered sled.
A musket is a muzzle-loaded, smoothbore fireairm, fired frae the shaulder.
The toga, a distinctive garment o Auncient Roum, wis a claith o aiblins 6 metres in lenth which wis wrapped aroond the body an wis generally worn ower a tunic.
The kimono is a Japanese tradeetional garment.
Baffies is a type o indoor fitweir, conseistin o a sole hauden tae the weirer's fit by a strap rinnin ower the taes or instep.
A lum hat is a flet-croun, braid-scruipt hat wuirn bi men an cleckit in the 1820s.
